title: Foreign Policy
new-page: true
is-card: true
tags: govt_affairs, cabinet
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; foreign_policy_timer += 6
view-if: CHP_in_government = 1 and foreign_minister_party = "CHP" and  foreign_policy_timer <= 0
card-image: img/portraits/TuranGunes.jpg
go-to: fp_menu

= Foreign Policy

Turkey is in the intersection of the global blocs and even though we are a member of NATO, we have to manage our relations with all our neighbors. There are four main partners we have to consider: The United States, Western Europe, The USSR and the Middle East.

Through our foreign policy initiatives we can secure trade agreements, loans and decide our level of integration in the Western alliance. CHP's foreign policy up until now has been one of armed non-interventionism, often summed up in Atatürk's saying '**Peace at home, peace in the world.**'. Even though since the 1950's the nation has moved towards the Western Alliance and NATO, decent and peaceful relations with all our neighbors is a key tenet of our foreign policy.

@fp_menu

- @west: Manage our relations with the West.
- @east: Manage our relations with the Soviets.
- @middleeast: Manage our relations with the Middle East.
- @root: No change to foreign policy.
- @easy_discard
- @cancel_advisor_action

@west

Turkey is a crucial member of the Western Alliance and of NATO. Our Western allies will act as the primary mediators of any diplomatic crisis arising concerning Turkey so maintaining decent ties is a necessity.

- @improve_us: Improve relations with the United States.
- @improve_west: Improve relations with Western Europe.
- @negotiategunes: Negotiate the Güneş Plan for the creation of a confederation in Cyprus with the US.
- @negotiatedenktas: Negotiate the Denktaş Plan for the creation of a confederation in Cyprus with the US.
- @aet: Apply to join the European Economic Community, EEC!
- @americanbase: As a reaction to the arms embargo, close the American bases in our soil!
- @fp_menu: Return to the foreign policy menu.

@improve_us
on-arrival: us_relation += 5

We improve our relations with the United States.

@improve_west
on-arrival: west_relation += 5

We improve our relations with Western Europe.

@negotiategunes
subtitle: The Güneş Plan is a plan for the reunification of Cyprus under a confederation created by our exterior minister Turan Güneş. The plan suggests splitting the island into many decentralized zones across the island along ethnic lines. We have to negotiate a deal before the US Congress approves an arms embargo against us at the end of the year!
view-if: cyprus_problem == 3 and year < 1975
choose-if: foreign_minister_party = "CHP"
on-arrival: gunesplan += 1

We negotiate the plan with our American counterparts who act as mediators between us and the Greeks. We have to sustain our efforts for a breakthrough in the negotiations.

@negotiatedenktas
subtitle: Even though we have lost our chance with the Güneş Plan, it may still be possible to find a peaceful end to the Cyprus Problem. The Denktaş Plan is a plan for the reunification of Cyprus under a confederation created by the Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktaş. The plan unlike the Güneş Plan entails a division of the island into two halves roughly along the invasion lines.
view-if: cyprus_problem == 3 and year >= 1975
choose-if: foreign_minister_party = "CHP" and us_relation > 40
unavailable-subtitle: Our relations with the US are not good enough to negotiate the Denktaş Plan!
on-arrival: denktasplan += 1

Despite the strained relations we make attempts at negotiating an end to the Cyprus problem.

@aet
subtitle: Even though we will probably not see the end of our application process in the 1970's, the application may greatly benefit our nation in the decades to come.
choose-if: economicreform == 1 and inflation < 20 and growth > 4 and unemployment < 10 and west_relation >= 70 and (cyprus_problem == 2 or cyprus_problem == 4)
unavailable-subtitle: We have not achieved the prequisites for an application yet! The prequisites we have to achieve are: a reform of the Turkish economy, decent economic figures, good relations with Western Europe, a peaceful end to the Cyprus problem.
on-arrival: aet += 1; democracystatus += 3
max-visits: 1

We have officially applied to join the ECC! Though it will take many years before our application opens the door for our membership, this is a great step for the future of Turkish Democracy.

@americanbase
choose-if: cyprus_problem == 3
on-arrival: rural_chp += 3; workers_chp += 3; state_employees_chp += 3; petty_bourgeoisie_chp += 3; alevis_chp += 3; us_relation -= 0.1
max-visits: 1

With the exception of the İncirlik base we closed down all the American bases in our country as a reaction to the arms embargo. Our people cherish this determination though our relations with the US has deteriorated even further.


@east
choose-if: z_in_goverment == 0 and DP_in_government == 0
unavailable-subtitle: Our coalition partners prevent us from fostering relations with the Soviets!

Up until now our relations with the Eastern Bloc have been cold at best. However after Stalin's death the Soviet attitude towards Turkey have shifted towards a reconciliatory direction. Even though we should keep our relations with the West in mind, we have a lot to gain from improved relations with the Soviet Union.

- @improve_east: Improve relations with the Soviet Union.
- @friendship: Sign a treaty of Turkish-Soviet Friendship.
- @credits: Borrow loans from the Soviet Union.
- @treaty: Sign a treaty of economic cooperation.
- @export: Export agricultural products to the Eastern Bloc.
- @romanianoil: Purchase oil from Romania.
- @fp_menu: Return to the foreign policy menu.

@improve_east
on-arrival: soviet_relation += 5

Even though we are on the other side of the Iron Curtain, the Soviet Union is our largest neighbor. We improve our relations with the Soviets.

@friendship
on-arrival: friendshipp += 1; soviet_relation += 10; us_relation -= 10; west_relation -= 5; growth_modifier += 0.5
choose-if: friendshipp == 0 and soviet_relation >= 35
unavailable-subtitle: [? if friendshipp > 0 : We have already signed a treaty of friendship! ?] [? if soviet_relation < 40 : Our relationship with the USSR is not decent enough! ?]

Despite our previous disagreements the Soviets have been willing to consider normalization. We have signed a treaty of 'Decent Neighborhood and Friendly Cooperation' with the Soviets which will faciliate diplomatic and economic ties between the two nations. If we intend to reconsider our current relationship with the USSR and move towards a positive direction we have to continue building up mutual cooperation. However our reconciliation with the USSR has brought significant backlash from the US and Western Europe. We have to walk on a thin thread if Ecevit is not to become another Allende.

@credits
on-arrival: budget += 2; us_relation -= 5; friendshipp += 1
choose-if: friendshipp == 1 and soviet_relation >= 50
view-if: friendshipp != 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if friendshipp < 1 : We need to normalize our relations through a friendship treaty first! ?] [? if soviet_relation < 50 : Our relationship with the USSR is not decent enough! ?]

We borrow a long term loan from the Soviet Union.

@treaty
on-arrival: growth_modifier += 0.7; unemployment_modifier -= 0.5; inflation_modifier += 1.5; us_relation -= 5; treatyy += 1
choose-if: friendshipp == 2 and soviet_relation >= 60 and treatyy == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [if treatyy == 1 : We have already signed a treaty of economic cooperation! ?] [? if friendshipp < 2 : We need to normalize our relations and increase economic cooperation by taking loans first! ?] [? if soviet_relation < 60 : Our relationship with the USSR is not decent enough! ?] 

A Turkish-Soviet economic cooperation treaty seals our efforts of reconciliation. Our economy will greatly benefit from this maneuver.

@export
on-arrival: agricultural_consumption += 4; inflation_modifier += 0.5; rural_chp += 1
choose-if: friendshipp == 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if friendshipp < 2 : We need to normalize our relations and increase economic cooperation by taking loans first! ?]

We establish the corridors for our farmers and landowners to sell agricultural products such as citrus and wheat, increasing demand for the increasing supply but also conversely increasing inflation.

@romanianoil
choose-if: friendshipp >= 1
on-arrival: forex_pressure -= 4; inflation_modifier -= 2; oil += 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if friendshipp < 1 : We need to normalize our relations through a friendship treaty first! ?] 
max-visits: 1

Turkey largely depends on foreign energy to power its growing industry and cities. Our dependence to oil in such a sense has destabilized our economy when the oil procies soured, like in the oil crisis of 1973. We safeguard our access to the the supply of oil to mitigate the effects of any future crisis.

@middleeast

The Middle East is currently roughly divided into two blocs, the Conservative Monarchies and the Socialist Pan-Arabists. However thankfully we do not have to pick a side and we should work towards fostering ties with both factions. The Gulf Monarchies have stronger relations with the US while conversely the Pan-Arabists are closer to the USSR, a factor we should keep in mind when improving relations. Due to the Iranian Monarchy's hostile attitude towards us, improving relations with them is not an option.

- @arabrelation: Improve relations with the Arabian States.
- @trade: Foster trade with the Arabian States.
- @panarab1: Increase economic ties with the Pan-Arabists.
- @panarab2: Increase economic ties with the Pan-Arabists.
- @monarchy1: Increase economic ties with the Gulf Monarchies.
- @monarchy2: Increase economic ties with the Gulf Monarchies.
- @fko: Form official relations with the Palestine Liberation Organization, PLO.
- @fp_menu: Return to the foreign policy menu.

@arabrelation
on-arrival: middle_east_relation += 5

We improve relations with the Gulf Monarchies and the Pan Arabists.

@trade
subtitle: Exporting agricultural products can act as a new stream of revenue.
choose-if: middle_east_relation >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: We have to improve our relations with the Arabian states first! 
on-arrival: tradee += 1; growth_modifier += 0.3; inflation_modifier -= 0.5; agricultural_consumption += 4; forex_pressure -= 2; rural_chp += 1

We increase our trade with our Arabian neighbors. By exporting agricultural products we are able to both decrease foreign exchange pressure and increase the revenues of our farmers. 

@panarab1
subtitle: As a first step we can acquire loans for purchasing oil.
choose-if: middle_east_relation >= 55 and tradee > 0
view-if: panarabb == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if middle_east_relation < 55 : We have to improve our relations with the Pan-Arabist nations first! ?] [? if tradee == 0 : We have to improve bilateral trade first! ?]
on-arrival: panarabb += 1; budget += 2; inflation_modifier -= 1; growth_modifier -= 0.4; oil += 1; forex_pressure -= 2

Oil loans allow us to build resistance for any future turbulence in global petrol prices. The payments however will have a negative impact on our economic growth.

@panarab2
subtitle: We can help the Pan-Arabists bypass Western sanctions by acting as a trade hub in-between.
choose-if: middle_east_relation >= 55 and tradee > 0
view-if: panarabb == 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if middle_east_relation < 55 : We have to improve our relations with the Pan-Arabist nations first! ?] [? if tradee == 0 : We have to improve bilateral trade first! ?]
on-arrival: inflation_modifier -= 0.5; growth_modifier += 0.4; us_relation -= 5

Acting as trade mediators boosts our growth and decreases inflation. However our assisting of the sanction bypassing does not go unnoticed by the US.

@monarchy1
subtitle: As a first step we can acquire loans for purchasing oil.
choose-if: middle_east_relation >= 55 and tradee > 0
view-if: monarchyy == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if middle_east_relation < 55 : We have to improve our relations with the Conservative Monarchies first! ?] [? if tradee == 0 : We have to improve bilateral trade first! ?]
on-arrival: monarchyy += 1; budget += 1; inflation_modifier -= 0.5; growth_modifier -= 0.4; oil += 1; forex_pressure -= 2

Oil loans allow us to build resistance for any future turbulence in global petrol prices. The payments however will have a negative impact on our economic growth.

@monarchy2
subtitle: We can send workers to bring in foreign currency. 
choose-if: middle_east_relation >= 55 and tradee > 0
view-if: monarchyy == 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if middle_east_relation < 55 : We have to improve our relations with the Conservative Monarchies first! ?] [? if tradee == 0 : We have to improve bilateral trade first! ?]
on-arrival: unemployment_modifier -= 0.4; inflation_modifier -= 0.5; forex_pressure -= 2

Through a series of agreements on temporary working permits, many of our unemployed citizens go to work in the Gulf Monarchies. 

@fko
subtitle: Many in CHP and Turkey as a whole are sympathethic to the Palestinian cause.
choose-if: fkoo == 0
unavailable-subtitle: We have already formed official relations with the PLA!
on-arrival: fkoo += 1; us_relation -= 10; west_relation -= 5; middle_east_relation += 10; rural_chp += 2; state_employees_chp += 2; workers_chp += 2; petty_bourgeoisie_chp += 2; alevis_chp += 2; msp_relation += 5; coalition_dissent -= 1 if msp_in_government == 1

Even though we are not a player in the Israel-Palestine conflict, recognizing the PLA as a legitimate actor can grant us popularity, stronger relations with the Middle East and possible easing down of the tensions with the internal Islamists. [? if msp_in_government == 1 : Erbakan supports this action as well which decreased coalition dissent. ?] Besides the pragmatic reasons, many on the left of our party are sympathethic to the Palestinian cause.


